'''約翰·托比'''（{{lang-en|John Tooby}}，{{bd|1952年|7月26日||}}）是[[美國|美國]][[人類學|人類學]]家，幫助[[心理學家|心理學家]]妻子[[勒達·科斯米德斯|勒達·科斯米德斯]]一起開拓[[演化心理學|演化心理學]]領域。<ref>[[David_Buss|David Buss]], in the textbook ''Evolutionary Psychology'' (Allyn & Bacon, 1999), pp. xxi-xxii: "In the writing of this book I owe the greatest intellectual debt to Leda Cosmides, John Tooby, Don Symons, Martin Daly, and Margo Wilson, pioneers and founders of the emerging field of evolutionary psychology."</ref><ref>See also Geoffrey Miller, "How to Keep Our Meta-Theories Adaptive: Beyond Cosmides, Tooby, and Lakatos" ''Psychological Inquiry'' 11:1 (2000), p. 42: "For a young science barely a decade old, evolutionary psychology has achieved a remarkably strong metatheoretical consensus. [...] [E]volutionary psychology's metatheory was also shaped very strongly by a series of ambitious, persuasive, and visionary articles by Cosmides and Tooby in the late 1980s and early 1990s that showed how adaptationism could be applied to the human mind.  The Cosmides-Tooby vision of evolutionary psychology profoundly influenced the thinking of other leading researchers, such as [[David_Buss|Buss]], [[Gerd_Gigerenzer|Gigerenzer]], [[Steven_Pinker|Pinker]], and [[Randy_Thornhill|Thornhill]]. It was also adopted as the conceptual framework in the most influential popular accounts of evolutionary psychology."</ref>

==生平==
出生於[[明尼蘇達州|明尼蘇達州]][[聖保羅_(明尼蘇達州)|聖保羅]]。1989年獲得[[哈佛大學|哈佛大學]]生物人類學博士學位，現為[[加利福尼亞大學聖塔芭芭拉分校|加利福尼亞大學聖塔芭芭拉分校]]人類學教授。1992年他與勒達·科斯米德斯、[[杰羅姆·巴考|杰羅姆·巴考]]共同著作《{{link-en|適應的心靈|The Adapted Mind|適應的心靈}}》。他與勒達·科斯米德斯共同創辦和指導{{link-en|演化心理學中心|Center for Evolutionary Psychology|演化心理學中心}}。他目前正在編寫一本關於有性生殖和遺傳系統演變的書。<ref>Last line of introductory paragraph on John Tooby's personal web page http://www.anth.ucsb.edu/faculty/tooby/ {{Wayback|url=http://www.anth.ucsb.edu/faculty/tooby/ |date=20161119154943 }}</ref>

